'''杯子'''，又稱'''盅'''，是一種用於盛裝[[液體|液體]]以供傾倒或飲用的開頂[[容器|容器]]。它主要用於飲用流体，也可用於儲存需要倒出以使用的固體物質如[[糖|糖]]、[[麵粉|麵粉]]、[[穀物|穀物]]等。<ref name=bbc1>{{cite web |author=Producer Chris |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/radio1movies/2009/12/who_drank_from_this.shtml |title=Radio 1 Movies Blog: Who Drank From This? |date=2009-12|publisher=BBC |accessdate=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924160659/http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/radio1movies/2009/12/who_drank_from_this.shtml |archive-date=2015-09-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/cup |title=Cup - Definition and More from the Free Merriam-Webster Dictionary |publisher=Merriam-webster.com |date=2012-08-31 |accessdate=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108021406/http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/cup |archive-date=2014-01-08 }}</ref>杯子可由[[玻璃|玻璃]]、[[金屬|金屬]]、[[瓷器|瓷器]]、[[粘土|粘土]]、[[木材|木材]]、[[岩石|石頭]]、[[聚苯乙烯|聚苯乙烯]]、[[塑膠|塑膠]]、[[鋁|鋁]]或其他材料製成<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/cup?s=t&path=/ |title=Cup | Define Cup at Dictionary.com |publisher=Dictionary.reference.com |accessdate= 2019-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007030928/http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/cup?s=t&path=%2F |archive-date=2015-10-07}}</ref>，通常會附有一個桿、[[把手|把手]]或其他裝飾品。在各種文化和社會階層中，杯子均用於解渴<ref>{{cite web |author=Producer Chris |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/radio1movies/2009/12/who_drank_from_this_the_answer.shtml |title=Radio 1 Movies Blog: Who Drank From This? The Answer |publisher=BBC |accessdate=2014-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924160700/http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/radio1movies/2009/12/who_drank_from_this_the_answer.shtml|date=2019-12 |archive-date=2015-09-24}}</ref>。不同風格的杯子可以用於盛放不同的液體、固體<ref name="wisegeek">{{cite web |url=http://www.wisegeek.com/what-are-the-different-types-of-coffee-cups.htm |title=What Are the Different Types of Coffee Cups? (with pictures) |publisher=Wisegeek.com |date=2014-01-28 |accessdate=2014-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201210150/http://www.wisegeek.com/what-are-the-different-types-of-coffee-cups.htm |archive-date=2014-02-01 }}</ref>，或用於不同的場合、裝潢<ref name="wisegeek"/>。

==歷史==
和使用手或腳以盛裝液體相比，使用杯子盛裝液體是更為明智的選擇<ref name="R1-573574">{{Cite book|author=Rigby, Stephen Henry|title=A Companion to Britain in the Later Middle Ages|edition=Illustrated|year=2003|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|isbn=978-0-631-21785-5|ref=R1}} p. 573–574.</ref>。幾乎可以肯定的是，在人類有記載的歷史之前，杯子就已經被製造和使用。在世界各地的考古遺址中，都發現過杯子<ref>{{cite book|title=Cultural Anthropology: The Human Challenge|author= Haviland, William A.|publisher=[[The_Thomson_Corporation|The Thomson Corporation]]|year=2004|isbn=978-0-534-62487-3|page=77}}</ref>
，這些杯子有的是用貝殼和挖空的石頭做成的。<ref>例如保存洞穴繪畫顏料的鏤空石頭（“參見”[[技術史#石器時代|技術史]]），以及用於盛裝化妝品的貽貝殼。在[[古埃及|古埃及]]的墓地中發現了亦這種樣式的杯子的遺跡。</ref>在古代[[美索不達米亞|美索不達米亞]]，人民製作各式杯子以滿足包括運輸和飲用酒精飲料在內的各種用途。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archaeologynewsnetwork.blogspot.com/2012/04/gold-cup-headlines-mesopotamia.html |title=The Archaeology News Network: Gold cup headlines Mesopotamia exhibition |publisher=Archaeologynewsnetwork.blogspot.com |date=2012-04-24|accessdate=2014-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130120171340/http://archaeologynewsnetwork.blogspot.com/2012/04/gold-cup-headlines-mesopotamia.html |archive-date=2013-01-20}}</ref>有證據表明，[[羅馬帝國|羅馬帝國]]可能將杯子傳播到整個歐洲，例如包括[[威爾士|威爾士]]的銀盃和古代[[色雷斯|色雷斯]]的變色玻璃杯。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.archaeology.org/0403/newsbriefs/romecup.html|title=Roman Cup - Archaeology Magazine Archive|date=2004-03|work=[[Archaeology_(magazine)|Archaeology]]|accessdate=2014-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202214524/http://archive.archaeology.org/0403/newsbriefs/romecup.html|archive-date=2014-02-02}}</ref><ref name="Merali">{{cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/this-1600-year-old-goblet-shows-that-the-romans-were-nanotechnology-pioneers-787224/|title=This 1,600-Year-Old Goblet Shows that the Romans Were Nanotechnology Pioneers|last=Merali|first=Zeeya|date=2013-09|work=[[Smithsonian_(magazine)|Smithsonian]]|accessdate=2014-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201203833/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/history/this-1600-year-old-goblet-shows-that-the-romans-were-nanotechnology-pioneers-787224/|archive-date=2014-02-01}}</ref>在[[英格蘭|英格蘭]]，人們發現了幾千年前的杯子，其中包括距今約3700年的[[里拉頓金杯|里拉頓金杯]]。在美洲，早在11-14世紀就已經有杯子出現<ref name="Norton">{{cite web|url=http://news.sciencemag.org/2012/08/starbucks-ancient-america|title=Starbucks of Ancient America?|last=Norton|first=Elizabeth|date=2012-08-06|work=[[ScienceNOW|ScienceNOW]]|accessdate=2014-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201170149/http://news.sciencemag.org/2012/08/starbucks-ancient-america|archive-date=2014-02-01}}</ref>，而在[[墨西哥灣|墨西哥灣]]周圍的美洲土著會將{{le|馬海螺|Triplofusus papillosus}}用作杯子和其它用途<ref>Atlantic City Aquarium, [http://www.acaquarium.com/animals/717/ Horse conch]{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140515011155/http://www.acaquarium.com/animals/717/ |date=2014-05-15 }}</ref>。

== 用途 ==
在家居方面，杯通常用來盛載飲料，如水、咖啡、牛奶和果汁，但湯一般用[[碗|碗]]承載。<ref name=bbc1/>
在梳洗時，杯也用來盛水以供漱口，這些杯多以膠製造，稱作“漱口杯”<ref>{{cite journal |author1=廖紫均 |title=淺談馬克杯的歷史 |journal=國立自然科學博物館館訊 |date=2017-07 |issue=356 |page=4 |url=http://web2.nmns.edu.tw/PubLib/NewsLetter/106/356/4.pdf |accessdate=2020-07-16 |publisher=國立自然科學博物館 |location=台中 |language=zh-tw |format=pdf |issn=1682-5225 |archive-date=2017-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722004626/http://web2.nmns.edu.tw/PubLib/NewsLetter/106/356/4.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在化学、生物、医学方面的[[实验室|实验室]]都可看到[[烧杯|烧杯]]，主要用来盛载实验容剂。<ref name=Zheng&Pan>{{cite book |editor=郑燕龙; 潘子昂 |title=实验室玻璃仪器手册 |url=http://www.scilib.org/o6-3%E5%AE%9E%E9%AA%8C%E5%AE%A4%E7%8E%BB%E7%92%83%E4%BB%AA%E5%99%A8%E6%89%8B%E5%86%8C-%E9%83%91%E7%87%95%E9%BE%99-%E6%BD%98%E5%AD%90%E6%98%82code-sz22033/ |format=PDF |edition=第1版第1次印刷 |date=2007-05 |publisher=化学工业出版社 |location=北京 |language=zh-cn |isbn=978-7-122-00168-9 |pages=1~4 |chapter=§1.1 |access-date=2016-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921062518/http://www.scilib.org/o6-3%E5%AE%9E%E9%AA%8C%E5%AE%A4%E7%8E%BB%E7%92%83%E4%BB%AA%E5%99%A8%E6%89%8B%E5%86%8C-%E9%83%91%E7%87%95%E9%BE%99-%E6%BD%98%E5%AD%90%E6%98%82code-sz22033/ |archive-date=2016-09-21 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>另外也有[[獎盃|獎盃]]，主要用于奖励冠军得主，其為一种荣誉证明或纪念品，并不能用于饮食，也有的奖杯（如[[世界杯足球赛|世界杯足球赛]]的[[大力神杯|大力神杯]]）已不像杯子。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Noto|first1=Suzanne|title=Loving Cup History|url=https://www.silvergallery.com/blog/loving-cup-history/|website=Silver Gallery|access-date=2020-07-16|archive-date=2020-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106125330/https://www.silvergallery.com/blog/loving-cup-history/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

